NIGERIAN OIL MINISTER RILWANU LUKMAN SAIDTODAY GOVERNMENT SUBSIDY ON DOMESTIC OIL PRODUCTS HAD RISENFROM 20 TO 85 PCT AFTER THE FLOTATION OF THE NAIRA CURRENCYLAST SEPTEMBER.    THE NAIRA HAS DEPRECIATED BY OVER 60 PCT AGAINST THE DOLLARSINCE IT WAS FLOATED AND THE GOVERNMENT SAYS PETROLEUM PRODUCTSHAD BECOME TOO CHEAP ENCOURAGING SMUGGLING TO NEIGHBOURINGSTATES.    LUKMAN TOLD REPORTERS DOMESTIC OIL PRICES WERE BEINGCRITICALLY STUDIED AND A DECISION WOULD BE TAKEN SOON ONWHETHER OR NOT TO REDUCE THE SUBSIDY.    LAST YEAR, THE GOVERNMENT CUT OIL SUBSIDY BY 80 PCT AS PARTOF ITS ECONOMIC ADJUSTMENT PROGRAM.    OIL FIRMS HAVE ARGUED THAT THE DEPRECIATION OF THE NAIRAHAS MADE FURTHER REMOVAL OF PETROLEUM SUBSIDY NECESSARY. Reuter&#3;